A car crashed into Glasgow Airport, causing chaos as people fled the scene.
British Prime Minister Gordon Brown confirmed it was a deliberate attack, raising the security threat level.
The incident was linked to a foiled car bomb plot in London.
The burning vehicle turned into a fireball, with one occupant shouting religious phrases.
Security measures were heightened at airports across the UK, with two arrests made in connection to the attacks.
The public was urged to stay vigilant as the nation faced a critical security alert.
